DataElement.preferredName: Double Microarray Data Column Order Value double One Dimensional Array
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A 64-bit floating point primitive. When wrapped in an immutable Object, it is called a Double.:A piece of glass or plastic on which different samples have been affixed at separate locations in an ordered manner thus forming a microscopic array.  The samples are usually DNA fragments but may also be antibodies, other proteins, or tissues.:A collection or single item of factual information, derived from measurement or research, from which conclusions may be drawn.:An arrangement of objects one under another in a line._A logical or comprehensible arrangement of separate elements; a condition of regular or proper arrangement.:A numerical quantity measured or assigned or computed._A generic value domain for a one dimensional array containing double-precision 64 bit floating point values having a format of an integer mantissa followed by an optional 'E' or 'e' and an integer exponent.
